frus:attachment.p:
Considering that it is desirable to adjust, as early as possible, the
                        collection of taxes in such a manner as to facilitate the future
                        establishment of the complete liberty of interior commerce;

Considering, finally, that the effects which, by this law, are to be taxed,
                        are those which really make the most use of the roads, and should,
                        therefore, supply the means for their repair;
